parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift erratically, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
loses power
or shifts erratically; transmission warning lights illuminate; difficulty shifting gears; vehicle stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift erratically, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal sticks to the floor
difficulty shifting gears
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: Oil levels drop rapidly
engine noise or knocking
engine warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
difficulty stopping
brake warning lights illuminate
brake failure while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause various problems, including stalling, loss of power, or failure of essential systems.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
loses power
or experiences electrical system failures; warning lights illuminate; difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the vehicle stalls
loses power
and experiences various malfunctions

power steering
and brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and clutch can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience difficulty shifting gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
and experiences difficulty shifting gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine and oil consumption can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience excessive oil consumption, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

loses power

the check engine light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment and electronic system can cause the vehicle to experience various malfunctions, which can lead to driver distraction and accidents.
symptoms: The touchscreen becomes unresponsive
the radio screen goes black

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the key fob and ignition can cause the vehicle to experience difficulty starting, and the key to become stuck in the ignition, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the vehicle has difficulty starting
and the key cannot be removed from the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls

or jerks while driving
the engine makes a knocking sound
the vehicle operates roughly
the oil level is low
the check engine light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving on the highway.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle hesitates or jerks
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle loses power
the power steering and power brakes are lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become stiff or hard to depress, leading to a loss of braking assist, which can increase the stopping distance and risk of a crash.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stiff or hard to depress
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
a hissing or air sound is heard when applying the brakes.
